##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "contextFraction.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

# the base
$a = random(2,10,1);

# the exponent
$n = random(2,3,1);

Context("LimitedFraction");
Context()->flags->set(showMixedNumbers=>0, requireProperFractions=>1);
$ans = Compute($a**$n);



##############################################
TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML
Here is an expression with negative exponents.

    [`
        \displaystyle\frac{1}{[$a]^{[$n*(-1)]}}=
     `][____________]{$ans}

Evaluate the expression; in other words, write the answer 
without using exponents. 

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

We evaluate the expression by remembering that [`x^{-n}`] is the same thing as [``\frac{1}{x^n}``] 
for any non-zero,
real value of [`x`]

    [`
      \begin{aligned}
            \frac{1}{[$a]^{[$n*(-1)]}} & = [$a]^{[$n]}\\
                             & = [$ans]
      \end{aligned}
    `]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
##############################################


ENDDOCUMENT();
